$ ctetra4_constrained_thermal.bdf
$ Six CTETRA4 (Kuhn cube) — uniaxial constrained thermal stress (z-direction)
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m × 1 m cube, 6 CTETRA4 (Kuhn decomposition)
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      fix T3 of ALL eight nodes — cube cannot expand in z
$           fix T1+T2 of node 1 and T2 of node 2 — lateral rigid-body prevention
$           Cube is free to contract/expand in x and y (Poisson effect)
$
$ Hand calculation (same as chexa8_constrained_thermal, z constrained, x/y free):
$   σ_z = -E*α*ΔT = -1000 Pa  (uniform in all elements)
$   σ_x = σ_y = 0
$   von Mises = 1000 Pa
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CTETRA4 CONSTRAINED THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
$ Nodes: unit cube
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,5,,0.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,6,,1.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,7,,1.0,1.0,1.0
GRID,8,,0.0,1.0,1.0
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
PSOLID,1,1
$ 6-tet Kuhn decomposition
CTETRA,1,1,1,2,3,7
CTETRA,2,1,1,5,6,7
CTETRA,3,1,1,4,8,7
CTETRA,4,1,2,1,6,7
CTETRA,5,1,5,1,8,7
CTETRA,6,1,4,1,3,7
$ Fix T3 (z) of all eight nodes — z-expansion constrained
SPC1,1,3,1
SPC1,1,3,2
SPC1,1,3,3
SPC1,1,3,4
SPC1,1,3,5
SPC1,1,3,6
SPC1,1,3,7
SPC1,1,3,8
$ Lateral rigid-body prevention
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C on all nodes
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
TEMP,1,5,100.0
TEMP,1,6,100.0
TEMP,1,7,100.0
TEMP,1,8,100.0
ENDDATA
